nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Histidine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network is anchored on the Shen-Or\u00f3 erythrose-formamidine pathway\u2014the only experimentally complete prebiotic route to histidine (3.5% yield). Pathway diversity is achieved through multiple convergent routes to the key intermediates: formaldehyde (3 hydrothermal/surface routes), erythrose (2 aldol routes via borate minerals), formamidine (2 routes via direct amidination or formamide intermediate), and imidazole-4-acetaldehyde (2 routes: direct Amadori cyclization or via co-produced imidazole-4-glycol). All routes converge at the final Strecker synthesis step. The Sutherland cyanosulfidic 2-aminoimidazole branch is included as a parallel imidazole-producing pathway that enriches the prebiotic imidazole pool but does not claim a direct speculative conversion to histidine. The network flows from hydrothermal C1 carbon fixation through surface sugar/heterocycle assembly to biochemical Strecker completion.\n\nMOLECULES (21 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: CHO2- (formate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CO (carbon monoxide) [starting]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H8O4 (D-erythrose) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: CH4N2 (formamidine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C5H6N2O (imidazole-4-acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H8N2O2 (imidazole-4-glycol) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C6H9N3O2 (L-histidine) [target]\n  - mol_016: N2 (nitrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_017: CH4 (methane) [starting]\n  - mol_018: CH2N2 (